# Cursor Rules for Industrial Maintenance Scheduler

## Code Style
- Follow PEP 8 style guide
- Use Black formatter with 88 character line length
- Use type hints for all function parameters and return values
- Use descriptive variable and function names

## Python Standards
- Use f-strings for string formatting
- Prefer pathlib.Path over os.path
- Use dataclasses for data structures
- Import order: standard library, third-party, local imports

## Project Structure
- Keep business logic in `app/services/`
- Keep domain models in `app/models/`
- Keep utilities in `app/utils/`
- Keep API routes in `app/main.py` (consider splitting into `app/routes/` if it grows)
